  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (b65d58d 2022-11-17T00:11:25.133141Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI'm trying to deploy a contract on multiple chains using `create2` with `forge script`. On Optimism mainnet, I'm getting an error that the create2 deployer is not found. \r\n\r\nHere is a minimal reproducible example. Run with `forge script Repro.s.sol --private-key ${PRIVATE_KEY} -vvvv --broadcast --tc Deploy2`\r\n\r\n```\r\n// forge script Repo.s.sol --private-key ${PRIVATE_KEY} -vvvv --broadcast --tc Deploy2\r\n// CREATE2 Deployer not present on this chain. [0x4e59b44847b379578588920ca78fbf26c0b4956c]\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.10;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\nimport \"forge-std/console.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract SampleContract {\r\n    uint256 public test;\r\n\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        test = 1;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Deploy2 is Script {\r\n    bytes32 mySalt = bytes32(uint256(1));\r\n\r\n\tfunction run() external {\r\n\r\n        string memory RPC_URL = \"https://mainnet.optimism.io\";\r\n        uint256 forkId = vm.createFork(RPC_URL);\r\n\r\n        vm.startBroadcast();\r\n        SampleContract sample = new SampleContract{salt: mySalt}();\r\n        vm.stopBroadcast();\r\n\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```",
